def display_side_by_side(dfs:list, captions:list):
    """Display tables side by side to save vertical space
    Input:
        dfs: list of pandas.DataFrame
        captions: list of table captions
    """
    output = ""
    combined = dict(zip(captions, dfs))
    for caption, df in combined.items():
        output += df.style.set_table_attributes("style='display:inline'").set_caption(caption)._repr_html_()
        output += "\xa0\xa0\xa0"
    display(HTML(output))

def RCB_DC_plot(data, xvalue, key, label):
    cf.set_config_file(theme='polar',sharing='public',offline=True)
    data.iplot(kind="bar",x = xvalue,
                  subplots=False,
                  sortbars=True,
                  keys = [key],
                  title=label,
                  theme="polar"
                  )

# Overall performnace in IPL
def runs_off_boundaries(total_score, batsmen_runs, runs_123s, crease_data):
    off_boundaries = total_score.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "total_score")
    batsmen_boundaries = batsmen_runs.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "runs_offboundaries")
    runs_1s_2s_3s = runs_123s.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "runs_1s2s3s")
    batsmen_balls_faced = total_score.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "balls_faced")
    
    on_crease_data_batsmen = crease_data.groupby(['batsman'])['on_crease_balls'].sum().reset_index(name = 'on_crease_balls')
   
    off_boundaries["balls_played"] = batsmen_balls_faced.balls_faced
    off_boundaries["runs_offboundaries"] = batsmen_boundaries.runs_offboundaries
    off_boundaries["runs_1s2s3s"] = runs_1s_2s_3s.runs_1s2s3s
    crease_data=[]
    for i in off_boundaries.batsman.unique():
        crease_data.append(on_crease_data_batsmen[on_crease_data_batsmen.batsman == i].on_crease_balls.values[0])
        
    off_boundaries["on_crease_balls"] = crease_data
    off_boundaries["SS"] = ((off_boundaries.runs_1s2s3s/off_boundaries.runs_offboundaries) +
                            (off_boundaries.balls_played/off_boundaries.on_crease_balls))/(off_boundaries.total_score)
    normalised_ss =[]
    for i in off_boundaries.batsman.unique():
        ss_n = ((off_boundaries[off_boundaries.batsman == i].SS.values[0] - off_boundaries.SS.min())/(off_boundaries.SS.max() - off_boundaries.SS.min()))
        normalised_ss.append(ss_n)
    
    off_boundaries["normalised_SS"] = normalised_ss
    off_boundaries.sort_values(by=['normalised_SS'], inplace=True, ascending=False)
    return off_boundaries
###############################################################################################################################
# Matchwise average
def matchwise_runs_off_boundaries(m_total_score, m_batsmen_runs, m_runs_123s, crease_data1):
    matchwise_off_boundaries = m_total_score.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "total_score")
    matchwise_batsmen_boundaries = m_batsmen_runs.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "runs_offboundaries")
    matchwise_runs_1s_2s_3s = m_runs_123s.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "runs_1s2s3s")
    matchwise_balls_faced = m_total_score.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "balls_faced")
    matchwise_on_crease_data_batsmen = crease_data1.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['on_crease_balls'].sum().reset_index(name = 'on_crease_balls')
   
    
    matchwise_off_boundaries["runs_offboundaries"] = matchwise_batsmen_boundaries.runs_offboundaries
    matchwise_off_boundaries["balls_played"] = matchwise_balls_faced.balls_faced
    matchwise_off_boundaries["runs_1s2s3s"] = matchwise_runs_1s_2s_3s.runs_1s2s3s
    matchwise_off_boundaries["on_crease_balls"] = matchwise_on_crease_data_batsmen.on_crease_balls
    matchwise_off_boundaries.runs_offboundaries.fillna(0, inplace = True)
    bats = [];tscore = [];of_boundaries =[];b_played = []; s2s3s=[]; crease_balls =[]
    
    for i in matchwise_off_boundaries.batsman.unique():
        batsmen_boundaries_data = matchwise_off_boundaries[matchwise_off_boundaries.batsman == i]
        bats.append(i)
        tscore.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.total_score.mean())
        of_boundaries.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.runs_offboundaries.mean())
        s2s3s.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.runs_1s2s3s.mean())
        crease_balls.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.on_crease_balls.mean())
        b_played.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.balls_played.mean())
        
    SS =  pd.DataFrame(list(zip(bats, tscore, of_boundaries, s2s3s, b_played, crease_balls)), 
               columns =['batsman', 'total_score', 'runs_offboundaries', 'runs_1s2s3s', 'balls_played', 'on_crease_balls' ])
    SS["SS"] = ((SS.runs_1s2s3s/SS.runs_offboundaries) + (SS.balls_played/SS.on_crease_balls))/(SS.total_score)
    
    normalised_ss1 =[]
    for i in SS.batsman.unique():
        ss_n1 = ((SS[SS.batsman == i].SS.values[0] - SS.SS.min())/(SS.SS.max() - SS.SS.min()))
        normalised_ss1.append(ss_n1)
    SS['normalised_SS'] = normalised_ss1
    SS.sort_values(by = ['SS'], inplace=True, ascending=False)
    return SS

# Overall performnace in IPL
def smash_rates(total_score, batsmen_runs):
    off_boundaries = total_score.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "total_score")
    batsmen_boundaries = batsmen_runs.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "no_offboundaries")
    batsmen_boundaries_6s = batsmen_runs[batsmen_runs.batsman_runs == 6].groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "no_offboundaries_6s")
    batsmen_balls_faced = total_score.groupby(['batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "balls_faced")
    
    off_boundaries["balls_played"] = batsmen_balls_faced.balls_faced
    off_boundaries["no_offboundaries"] = batsmen_boundaries.no_offboundaries
    off_boundaries["no_offboundaries_6s"] = batsmen_boundaries_6s.no_offboundaries_6s
    off_boundaries["Smash_rate"] = (off_boundaries.no_offboundaries/off_boundaries.balls_played)*100

    return off_boundaries
###############################################################################################################################
# Matchwise average
def matchwise_smash_rates(m_total_score, m_batsmen_runs):
    matchwise_off_boundaries = m_total_score.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "total_score")
    matchwise_batsmen_boundaries = m_batsmen_runs.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "no_offboundaries")
    
    batsmen_boundaries_6s = m_batsmen_runs[m_batsmen_runs.batsman_runs == 6].groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "no_offboundaries_6s")
    matchwise_balls_faced = m_total_score.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "balls_faced")
    
    
    matchwise_off_boundaries["no_offboundaries"] = matchwise_batsmen_boundaries.no_offboundaries
    matchwise_off_boundaries["no_offboundaries_6s"] = batsmen_boundaries_6s.no_offboundaries_6s
    matchwise_off_boundaries["balls_played"] = matchwise_balls_faced.balls_faced
    matchwise_off_boundaries.no_offboundaries.fillna(0, inplace = True)
    bats = [];tscore = [];of_boundaries =[];b_played = []; no_6s = []
    
    for i in matchwise_off_boundaries.batsman.unique():
        batsmen_boundaries_data = matchwise_off_boundaries[matchwise_off_boundaries.batsman == i]
        bats.append(i)
        tscore.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.total_score.mean())
        of_boundaries.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.no_offboundaries.mean())
        no_6s.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.no_offboundaries_6s.mean())
        b_played.append(batsmen_boundaries_data.balls_played.mean())
        
    smash_rate =  pd.DataFrame(list(zip(bats, tscore, of_boundaries,  b_played, no_6s)), 
               columns =['batsman', 'total_score', 'no_offboundaries',  'balls_played', 'no_offboundaries_6s'])
    
    smash_rate["smash_rate"] = (smash_rate.no_offboundaries/smash_rate.balls_played)*100
    smash_rate.no_offboundaries_6s.fillna(0, inplace = True)
    smash_rate.sort_values(by = "smash_rate", inplace = True, ascending =  False)
    return smash_rate

# Overall performnace in IPL
def boundary_leaker(total_score2, batsmen_runs2):
    boundaries_given = batsmen_runs2.groupby(['bowler'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "no_offboundaries")
    bowlers_BL = total_score2.groupby(['bowler'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "balls_bowled")
    
    bowlers_BL["no_offboundaries"] = boundaries_given.no_offboundaries
    bowlers_BL.no_offboundaries.fillna(0, inplace =True)
    bowlers_BL['X'] = (bowlers_BL.balls_bowled/(bowlers_BL.no_offboundaries +1))
    bowlers_BL["BL"] = 1/(bowlers_BL.balls_bowled/(bowlers_BL.no_offboundaries +1))
                          
    return bowlers_BL
###############################################################################################################################
# Matchwise average
def matchwise_boundary_leaker(m_total_score2, m_batsmen_runs2):
    matchwise_batsmen_boundaries = m_batsmen_runs2.groupby(['match_id','bowler'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "no_offboundaries")
    matchwise_BL = m_total_score2.groupby(['match_id','bowler'])['batsman_runs'].count().reset_index(name = "balls_bowled")
    
    matchwise_BL["no_offboundaries"] = matchwise_batsmen_boundaries.no_offboundaries
    matchwise_BL.no_offboundaries.fillna(0, inplace = True)
    bowls = [];of_boundaries =[];b_bowled = [];
    
    for i in matchwise_BL.bowler.unique():
        bowler_boundaries_data = matchwise_BL[matchwise_BL.bowler == i]
        bowls.append(i)
        of_boundaries.append(bowler_boundaries_data.no_offboundaries.mean())
        b_bowled.append(bowler_boundaries_data.balls_bowled.mean())
        
    boundary_leaker =  pd.DataFrame(list(zip(bowls, of_boundaries, b_bowled)), 
               columns =['bowler', 'no_offboundaries',  'balls_bowled'])
    
    boundary_leaker['X'] = (boundary_leaker.balls_bowled/(boundary_leaker.no_offboundaries +1))
    boundary_leaker["BL"] = 1/(boundary_leaker.balls_bowled/(boundary_leaker.no_offboundaries +1))
 

    boundary_leaker.sort_values(by = "X", inplace = True, ascending =  False)
    return boundary_leaker

def wickets_taken(wickets_data_matchwise, match_data):
    for i in wickets_data_matchwise.bowler.unique():
        bowler.append(i)
        wi.append(round(wickets_data_matchwise[wickets_data_matchwise.bowler ==i].wickets.mean(),1))
        more_wickets.append(len(wickets_data_matchwise[wickets_data_matchwise.bowler ==i][wickets_data_matchwise.wickets >1].match_id.unique()))
        wicket_matches.append(len(wickets_data_matchwise[wickets_data_matchwise.bowler ==i].match_id.unique()))
        
        t_matches.append(len(match_data[match_data.bowler == i].match_id.unique()))
        
    wickets_data = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(bowler, wi, t_matches, wicket_matches, more_wickets)), 
               columns =['bowler','wickets','matches', 'wicket_matches', "> 1 wicket"])
    wickets_data["wickets %"] = (wickets_data.wicket_matches/wickets_data.matches)*100
    wickets_data["more than 1 wickets %"]= (wickets_data["> 1 wicket"]/wickets_data.wicket_matches)*100

    return wickets_data
